** About the business **

Austech Precision Engineering is a family owned and operated business
established in 2012 providing machining services mainly in mining, automotive
and material handling industries.

** About the role **

This is a full-time permanent position with variety of interesting work and
opportunities for further training and growth. We are currently invested on
new milling & lathe machines.

** Role Requirements: **

  * Program, set & operate CNC Milling and CNC Lathe machines. 
  * Preferred Fanuc Programming knowledge 
  * Train and mentor Apprentices 
  * Understand and adhere to strict workplace health & safety measures 
  * Must have a current resume with two work-related references 
  * Be available to commence employment ASAP 
  * Must be reliable and able to commit to a 5-day working week 

** Applicant Requirements **

  * Must have 3+ years of experience 
  * Punctuality, reliability, efficiency & sound work ethic 
  * Self-motivated and attention to detail 
  * Ability to follow instructions 
  * Works well in a team environment 
  * Has the ability to multi-task 
  * MUST be Australian citizen or have permanent residency status and work rights. 

